        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 4:32PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 432 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Maxwelton, or near Lewisburg, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lewisburg...
Ronceverte...
Renick...
Falling Spring...
Asbury...
Beartown State Park...
and Greenbrier River Trail.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
